 @Poojabariyarvlogs  Thank you, For the last 15–20 years, I have had a corporate health insurance cover of ₹10 lakh. In addition, after COVID in 2020, I took an ICICI Lombard health insurance policy of ₹50 lakh, which we have never used.
Your incident has really made me rethink my own insurance, especially on what basis the claim was declined. I have used the corporate insurance three times for my mother Small, but for myself, my wife, and my son, we have never made any claim.
One more question - have you taken any claim for your husband from any other insurance policy? As far as I know, all insurance companies require disclosure of claims to a common insurance database (Insurance Information Bureau of India (IIB)).
